From adda3cd48bcdada36989332717011c3c233537a6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alex MKX <github-alex@xxl.cx>
Date: Mon, 25 May 2026 16:10:04 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] opencode: route subagent dispatches to named
 @implementer/@code-reviewer agents
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replaces hardcoded `general-purpose` agent dispatch in subagent prompt
templates with OpenCode named-agent references, with soft fallback to
`general-purpose` when the named agent isn't configured.

This lets users pin specific models per role via opencode.json agent
definitions, e.g.:

  agent:
    implementer:    { model: github-copilot/claude-sonnet-4.6 }
    code-reviewer:  { model: github-copilot/claude-sonnet-4.6,
                      fallback_models: [anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6, ...] }

All review roles (code-quality, spec-compliance, plan-doc, spec-doc) route
to @code-reviewer for simplicity — pin to the same model or override per
role in opencode.json as needed.
